On offense, San Francisco's quarterback Colin Kaepernick is one of the most agile and mobile in the league. I think he is the best of this new breed of quarterbacks. With the read option, he doesn't mind being hit or tackled, a bit like Panthers quarterback Cam Newton. Kaepernick is like a 12th man on the field because he has the capability to run down the field. That is something the Broncos defense will have to adjust to.

If DeMarcus Ware and Von Miller can contain the outside then it should be easier for the Denver defense to keep Kaepernick in the pocket. But it is always difficult for teams to do that because he is such a good runner of the football.

The 49ers have got so much talent. I tried to read up on what is going on in their locker room and it may just be the way coach Jim Harbaugh relays his tactics and speaks to his team.

